rentHistory.title: To Kill a Mockingbird
rentHistory.author: Harper Lee
rentHistory.description: A Pulitzer Prize-winning novel set in the Deep South and inspired by the author's own experiences, about a young girl named Scout and her father, a lawyer who defends a black man falsely accused of rape.

rentHistory.author: George Orwell
rentHistory.description: A dystopian novel set in a future totalitarian society, where the government monitors every aspect of citizens' lives and manipulates information to control them.

wishlist.title: The Great Gatsby
wishlist.author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
wishlist.description: The story of the mysteriously wealthy Jay Gatsby and his love for the beautiful Daisy Buchanan, set in the Jazz Age of the 1920s.
